cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a real-time RGB-based pipeline for object detection and 6D pose estimation using a novel 3D orientation estimation method based on a variant of the Denoising Autoencoder. The paper focuses on computer vision and robotics, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the advantages of the Augmented Autoencoder, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category.
